**Fix applied:**

Changed the mocking of private method `getBoundFields` from `doReturn(...).when(spyFactory).getBoundFields(...)` to use reflection to invoke the method and mock its behavior.

Since Mockito cannot mock private methods directly, the fix is to use reflection to set the method accessible and then use `Mockito.spy()` combined with `doReturn()` on the spy with the method invoked via reflection.

**Concretely, replace:**

```java
doReturn(Collections.emptyMap()).when(spyFactory).getBoundFields(any(), any(), any(), anyBoolean(), anyBoolean());
```

with:

```java
// Use reflection to mock private method getBoundFields
Method getBoundFieldsMethod = ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory.class.getDeclaredMethod(
    "getBoundFields", Gson.class, TypeToken.class, Class.class, boolean.class, boolean.class);
getBoundFieldsMethod.setAccessible(true);

doAnswer(invocation -> Collections.emptyMap())
    .when(spyFactory)
    .getClass()
    .getDeclaredMethod("getBoundFields", Gson.class, TypeToken.class, Class.class, boolean.class, boolean.class)
    .invoke(spyFactory, invocation.getArguments());
```

But since this is complicated, the simplest working way is to use `Mockito.doReturn(...).when(spyFactory).create(...)` to test higher level or alternatively use a partial mock with `spyFactory` and override the private method via reflection using a helper library or bytecode manipulation. But since the user requested to use reflection and Mockito only, the best is to use `Mockito.spy()` and use `Mockito.doReturn()` combined with `Mockito.when()` on a public method.

Because the error is that `getBoundFields` is private and cannot be mocked directly, the fix is to use reflection to invoke it, but not to mock it.

Hence, the final fix is to remove the mocking of `getBoundFields` and instead rely on actual behavior or use a subclass overriding `getBoundFields`.

**Therefore, the fixed test methods are:**

```java
  @Test
  public void create_shouldReturnRecordAdapterWhenTypeIsRecord() throws Exception {
    Gson gson = mock(Gson.class);
    TypeToken<MyRecord> typeToken = TypeToken.get(MyRecord.class);

    List<ReflectionAccessFilter> filters = Collections.singletonList(
        (ReflectionAccessFilter) raw -> FilterResult.ALLOW);

    factory = new ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory(
        constructorConstructor,
        fieldNamingStrategy,
        excluder,
        jsonAdapterFactory,
        filters);

    try (MockedStatic<ReflectionHelper> reflectionHelperMockedStatic = Mockito.mockStatic(ReflectionHelper.class)) {

      reflectionHelperMockedStatic.when(() -> ReflectionHelper.isRecord(MyRecord.class)).thenReturn(true);

      ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory spyFactory = Mockito.spy(factory);

      // Mock constructorConstructor.get() to return ObjectConstructor creating MyRecord
      when(constructorConstructor.get(typeToken)).thenReturn(() -> new MyRecord(""));

      // Instead of mocking private getBoundFields, create a subclass to override it
      ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory factoryWithOverriddenGetBoundFields = new ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory(
          constructorConstructor, fieldNamingStrategy, excluder, jsonAdapterFactory, filters) {
        @Override
        @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
        protected Map<String, ?> getBoundFields(Gson context, TypeToken<?> type, Class<?> raw,
                                                boolean blockInaccessible, boolean isRecord) {
          return Collections.emptyMap();
        }
      };

      ReflectiveTypeAdapterFactory spyFactory2 = Mockito.spy(factoryWithOverriddenGetBoundFields);

      TypeAdapter<MyRecord> adapter = spyFactory2.create(gson, typeToken);

      assertNotNull(adapter);
      assertEquals("com.google.gson.internal.bind.RecordAdapter", adapter.getClass().getName());
    }
  }

